I’m going to talk about my best friend’s home, which is a place I visit quite often.

He’s actually my next-door neighbor, and we’ve lived side by side for many years. Because of that, I drop by his place several times a week, usually to study together or just hang out.

His house was completely refurbished about two years ago, so it now looks very modern and stylish. It’s a three-storey terraced house with white as the dominant color, which gives it a clean and elegant appearance. At the front, there’s a wooden gate and a small yard. One side is filled with various plants grown by his parents, while the other is used as a parking space.

As you walk through the glass front door, you’re immediately struck by the sophisticated interior design and the high-quality furniture. The living room features a comfortable sofa set facing a large flat-screen TV mounted on the wall. The kitchen is fully equipped with modern appliances, and in the center, there’s a spacious dining table where the whole family gathers for meals.

The house has four bedrooms in total, and each one comes with its own bathroom, which makes it extremely convenient. One thing I really love is the presence of greenery—there are potted plants placed throughout the house, creating a fresh and relaxing atmosphere. The lighting is also very well designed, with ceiling lights arranged in a way that is both aesthetic and practical.

Overall, it’s a home that has almost everything I could ask for. Spending time there always makes me feel comfortable and relaxed, and it’s definitely the kind of place I hope to have for myself in the future.
